250 g Ground Beef
2 unit(s) Sandwich Bun
1 unit(s) Gala Apple
56 g Red Cabbage, shredded
90 mL Dill Pickle, sliced
4 tbsp BBQ Sauce
4 tbsp Mayonnaise
1 tbsp BBQ Seasoning
1 tbsp Whole Grain Mustard
1 unit(s) Honey
0.13 tsp Salt*
1.5 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Sugar*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then beef. Cook, breaking up beef into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.**
Carefully drain and discard excess fat, then stir in BBQ seasoning and BBQ sauce. Cook, stirring often, until well coated, 30 sec. Season with salt and pepper.
Cover to keep warm.

Meanwhile, core, then cut apple into 1/4-inch matchsticks.
Drain pickles over a small bowl.
Add 1/8 tsp (1/4 tsp) sugar and 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) mayo to the same bowl with pickle brine, season with pepper, then whisk to combine.
In a medium bowl, add cabbage and season with salt.
Using your hands, massage cabbage until slightly tender, 1 min.
Drizzle with brine-mayo mixture and add apples. Toss together. Set aside.

Add mustard, half the honey (use all for 4 ppl) and remaining mayo to another small bowl.
Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.

Halve sandwich buns.
Arrange directly on the top rack of the oven, cut-side up.
Toast buns until golden-brown, 3-4 min. (TIP: Keep an eye on buns so they don't burn!)

Spread hon ey-mustard mayo on sandwich buns.
Top bottom bun s with pickles and BBQ beef. Finish with top bu ns.
Divide BBQ beef sandwiches and cabbage-apple slaw between plates.

If you've opted to get beef, heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then beef. Cook, breaking up beef into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.** Carefully drain and discard excess fat. Add BBQ Seasoning and BBQ sauce. Cook, stirring often, until well coated, 30 sec. Season with salt and pepper, then cover to keep warm. Proceed with the recipe as written.